span.p:
Notes:
• Writes: Buffer -> WAL (durable) -> In-memory segment (searchable after refresh) -> Flush/Merge to disk
• Queries: Planner selects shards + predicates; only needed segment slices/pages are read (lazy/batched)
• Caching: Hot segments & postings stay in OS page cache; heap used for operators/results
• Vector: Only relevant graph/centroids loaded for current query (KNN/ANN)
• Stability: Heap size is critical—intermediate/final results dominate memory
• GC: G1/ZGC recommended; tune pause goals to match workload SLA
